Posttraumatic progressive myelopathy. Clinical and radiologic correlation employing MR imaging, delayed CT metrizamide myelography, and intraoperative sonography. Posttraumatic progressive myelopathy (PTPM) was studied in nine patients and grouped into three categories on the basis of characteristic radiographic findings and response to therapy: (a) myelomalacia with no cystic degeneration, which has poor response to therapy (b) small cysts, with poor response to therapy